    <h2 class="main-heading">PRIVACY POLICY AND CONSENT FOR THE USE OF DATA</h2>
    <p class="snippet">This Privacy Policy and Consent for the Use of Data (the “Policy”) explains the use of the information Customers provide to Aeropost, Inc. (“AP” or “ Aeropost”) the owners of the information (whether, a natural person, supplier, contractor, employee or any other person by virtue of any relationship with Aeropost), regardless of whether it was provided in connection with purchases, when visiting our website or by any other means. This Policy allows you to make informed decisions about whether to provide us with your personal information and also informs you of the opportunity to instruct us to limit how we use your personal information.</p>

    <h3 class="heading">Our Purpose:</h3>
    <p class="snippet">Aeropost believes it is important to protect the privacy of customers and other owners of personal information. We collect and use your information, including your name, contact information, mailing address, other identifying information, purchase history, etc. solely in order to provide you with better service and fulfill our corporate mission.</p>

    <h3 class="heading">Your Consent:</h3>
    <p class="snippet">By using our website in any way, you are taking an unambiguous act that allows us to reasonably conclude that you agree to our use of your data and that you have agreed to the terms and conditions outlined in this Policy.</p>

    <h3 class="heading">Collection of personal data and security:</h3>
    <p class="snippet">
        You provide, we obtain and may store your personal information within the scope of use described in this document, when you:
        <ul class="ml-10 list-disc my-4">
            <li>Purchase products or services through the AP website;</li>
            <li>Create an account to make purchases on Aeropost.com or subscribe to receive news or notifications from Aeropost;</li>
            <li>Place an order on Aeropost.com;</li>
            <li>Maintain a business relationship with Aeropost.com or</li>
            <li>Communicate with us for any other reason, whether by email, telephone, fax, in writing or in person at one of our offices.</li>
        </ul>
        We use commercially reasonable efforts to protect such information from unauthorized access, loss, misuse or alteration through technical, contractual, physical and administrative measures.
    </p>

    <h3 class="heading">Additional Online Data Collection and Related Security:</h3>
    <p class="snippet">When you visit our website, we may automatically collect information that helps us recognize you and helps us provide you with better service including, but not limited to, your computer's network address and system operational; the site from which you linked to us, your site activity, and the time and date of your visit and purchases. In a confidential and responsible manner, we collect, process and maintain some payment information in accordance with the data security regulations adopted by credit card companies, such as Visa, MasterCard and American Express. This means that we do not retain full credit card numbers, debit card PIN numbers, or credit card security codes, and each time we store the last four digits of a credit card number , we use appropriate encryption and access controls to protect them. If you use our website, any transmission of your data will be protected by Secure Socket Layer (SSL) or Transport Layer Security (TLS) encrypted encryption technologies.</p>


    <h3 class="snippet">Use, storage and disclosure of your personal data:</h3>
    <p class="snippet">
        Aeropost uses the personal information it collects to process your orders or transactions to follow up on any requests or comments you have, to provide quality customer service and to understand your shopping needs in order to provide you with a better service. We may use your personal information to offer you promotional information, products and services, and special notifications. In the case of employees and suppliers, Aeropost uses your personal information to process payments, support internal and external audit processes and for additional purposes to improve the relationship between you and Aeropost.
        <br><br>
        If you apply or request some products, offers or services, the personal information provided may be shared directly with third parties that provide the products, offers or services requested. Affiliated third parties with whom we may share information must not use the personal information we share with them for purposes other than providing the services we request from them. Since we are not responsible for any additional information you provide directly to these third parties, you should familiarize yourself with their privacy and security policies and practices before disclosing any information to them. We are not responsible for any information you provide to third parties. If you provide additional information to third parties, they (subject to applicable laws and their privacy policies) may share with us the information you provided to them and information about how you use the services. Additionally, if we terminate our relationship with the third party, the information you provided to them may be released to us and we may release it to a new third party that offers the same or similar services.
        <br><br>
        In addition, we may disclose personal information when doing so is reasonably necessary to comply with legal process or the authorities, respond to any demands or to protect the rights, property or personal safety of Aeropost, our customers, employees or the public. Information about our customers, including personal information, may be disclosed or transferred as part of or during negotiations of any merger, sale of company assets, or acquisition.
        <br><br>
        Similarly, we may transfer or transmit (as applicable) your personal data to other companies abroad for security, administrative, efficiency and to provide a better service, unless you instruct us otherwise. Aeropost has adopted these measures so that these companies implement, in their jurisdiction and in accordance with applicable laws, security standards and personal data protection similar to those stipulated in this document and Aeropost's policies in general. Additionally, we allow ourselves to inform you that if we no longer need to process your data, we can delete it from our databases.   
    </p>

    <h3 class="snippet">Third Party Data and Aggregate Data:</h3>
    <p class="snippet">
        In accordance with agreements between Aeropost and third parties, Aeropost may match user information with third party data. Aeropost may also disclose aggregate member statistics (i.e. percentage of female shoppers, percentage of online users) for the purpose of describing our business or services to prospective partners, advertisers and other third parties and for other lawful purposes. .
    </p>

    <h3 class="snippet">
        Use of Cookies:
    </h3>
    <p class="snippet">
        Cookies are alphanumeric identifiers that we transfer to your computer's hard drive through your web browser that help us identify you when you visit our website. You can make choices regarding cookies. By modifying your browsing preferences, you have the option to accept all cookies, to be notified when a cookie or to reject all cookies. If you choose to reject all cookies, you will not be able to use Aeropost's services (ie, make purchases online at Aeropost.com), which require registration in order to participate.
    </p>



    <h3 class="snippet">As a provider of personal data in relation to Aeropost, you can:</h3>
    <p class="snippet">
        a. Review and ask us to update, modify or delete your personal information;<br>
        b. Receive additional information, upon request, regarding the use of personal data;<br>
        c. Revoke (eventually) an express authorization to process the information;<br>
        d. Access your personal data processed during the last year.<br>
    </p>

    <h3 class="heading">How to contact Aeropost to restrict the way your personal data is used?</h3>
    <p class="snippet">Subject to the foregoing, you may instruct us not to send you any promotional offers or other marketing communications or request that we otherwise limit the use and distribution of your personal information. Although the information is collected, you can restrict how it is used. Please use the address provided below for this purpose.</p>
    
    
    <h3 class="snippet">Google Analytics:</h3>
    <p class="snippet">Aeropost uses Google Analytics analysis tools to analyze traffic to this website. Google Analytics does not create individual profiles of visitors and only collects data in the aggregate. For more information about Google Analytics, click on the following link: <a href="http://www.google.com/analytics/" class="text-bold">http://www.google.com/analytics/</a> </p>

    <h3 class="heading">How can you access or correct your information?</h3>
    <p class="snippet">You have the right to access your personally identifiable information held by Aeropost. You may correct factual errors in such information by submitting a request to us truthfully proving the error. To protect your privacy and security, we will take reasonable steps to verify your identity before granting access or making corrections.</p>

    <h3 class="heading">Questions or inquiries:</h3>
    <p class="snippet">
        If you have questions or inquiries about this Policy or any other aspect of this website or would like to contact us for any reason, please contact us at service@aeropost.com.
        <br><br>
        This Policy may be modified at any time or for any reason. It is considered to be valid from the date of publication on the website. For this reason, we recommend that you review our website periodically so that you are informed of any changes.
    </p>
    
